      "role": "user",
      "content": "exactly. but it's more than just \"arbitrage.\" i'm seeing consistent, massive clusters of liquidity that only activate during specific latency spikes. it's not just noise. it's like the metadata is being used as a secondary ledger to move billions outside the gaze of any central bank or regulator. if you look at the packet headers, the value is essentially encoded in the structure of the communication itself. how would a system even begin to track wealth if the \"money\" is just the way the data is organized?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
